4. Add `el1_flush_current` and patch `trap.S:92-95` to insert `bl el1_flush_current` between `bl do_ipc` and `b el1_return_to_user`. Also patch `sched::reschedule` and `sched::run` to call `flush_deliver_msg`. `cargo check`.
5. Add `install_stub_privs` (either in a new `proc/priv.rs` or as a `pub` fn in `proc/table.rs`).
6. Rewrite `kernel/src/arch/aarch64/user_stub.S` with the two stubs.
7. Update `kernel/src/arch/aarch64/userland.rs`: two `USER_CODE_PAGE_*`, two extern symbol pairs, two map_4k + copy + flush_icache loops, call `install_stub_privs`, set `p.priv_id` in `populate_stub_slot`.
8. Run host unit tests: `cargo test --workspace`. Then build & boot: `cargo kernel-aarch64 && timeout 8 cargo run -p minix4-kernel --target aarch64-unknown-none --release | tee /tmp/slice25.log`.

## 13. Test plan

**Unit tests.** All inline `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` in the new ipc modules. The slice-style refactor: every `mini_*` primitive takes `&mut [Proc; N_PROC_SLOTS]` so a test can build its own fixed-size `[Proc::EMPTY; N_PROC_SLOTS]` (already constructible) and exercise the primitive without touching `PROC_TABLE`. Helper:

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
fn test_table() -> Box<[Proc; N_PROC_SLOTS]> {
    // host-only — `Box` is allowed under `#[cfg(test)]` which builds against
    // libstd.
    let mut t = vec![Proc::EMPTY; N_PROC_SLOTS].into_boxed_slice();
    // ... helper to set up a few slots with deterministic nr/endpoint/priv_id.
    t.try_into().unwrap()
}
```

Specific tests:
| Module | Test | Asserts |
|---|---|---|
| send.rs | `send_immediate_delivery_to_specific_receiver` | dst was `RTS_RECEIVING` w/ `getfrom_e=caller`; after `mini_send`, dst.misc_flags has `MF_DELIVERMSG`, dst.rts==0, dst.deliver_msg.m_type matches input, returns `OK`. |
| send.rs | `send_immediate_delivery_to_any_receiver` | same with `getfrom_e=ANY`. |
| send.rs | `send_blocks_when_dst_not_ready` | caller.rts has `RTS_SENDING`, caller.send_msg matches, dst.caller_q == Some(caller_nr), returns `OK`. |
| send.rs | `sendnb_returns_enotready` | `SendFlags::NonBlocking` + non-receiving dst → returns `ENOTREADY`, caller.rts unchanged. |
| send.rs | `send_self_returns_edeadsrcdst` | sending to own endpoint → deadlock_check fires. |
| send.rs | `send_ipc_to_violation` | caller's `ipc_to` bit clear for dst → `ECALLDENIED`. |
| receive.rs | `receive_from_queued_sender_specific` | populate caller_q with one sender matching `src_e`; expect copy, sender unblocked, queue empty. |
| receive.rs | `receive_from_queued_sender_any` | `src_e=ANY` picks the FIFO head. |
